00:45:24.610 --> 00:45:27.760
being the trial way in.

00:45:27.760 --> 00:45:30.160
And they're also seeing
the users who never would

00:45:30.160 --> 00:45:32.230
have made any money for them.

00:45:32.230 --> 00:45:33.940
Which, by the way, in
most of these games

00:45:33.940 --> 00:45:36.762
tends to be an awful
lot of those users.

00:45:36.762 --> 00:45:38.220
They're watching
rewarded ads which

00:45:38.220 --> 00:45:41.240
means they're generating
advertising revenue.

00:45:41.240 --> 00:45:42.160
So this is where--

00:45:42.160 --> 00:45:43.870
this breaks the mold.

00:45:43.870 --> 00:45:47.500
Like, this is not a
pure, oh, show ads,

00:45:47.500 --> 00:45:48.810
user experience declines.

00:45:48.810 --> 00:45:50.740
That's not necessarily
what's happening here.

00:45:50.740 --> 00:45:53.590
In fact, we're seeing a drive
towards better monetization.

00:45:53.590 --> 00:45:56.620
And that's just really
terrific to see.

00:45:56.620 --> 00:45:57.120
OK.

00:45:57.120 --> 00:45:59.310
So let's move on to
tip number three.

00:45:59.310 --> 00:46:01.303
So non-spending players.

00:46:01.303 --> 00:46:03.220
So this has been the
really interesting piece.

00:46:03.220 --> 00:46:03.840
And I'll go back--

00:46:03.840 --> 00:46:06.507
two years ago I was talking to a
number of different publishers,

00:46:06.507 --> 00:46:10.080
developers around, hey, we know
you make a lot of money on IAP,

00:46:10.080 --> 00:46:12.050
but really how much?

00:46:12.050 --> 00:46:15.720
And we heard things
from 1%, 3%, 5%, 10%.

00:46:15.720 --> 00:46:18.120
That's the number
of users in my base,

00:46:18.120 --> 00:46:20.560
or the percentage
where I'm making money.

00:46:20.560 --> 00:46:22.320
It turns out the rest--

00:46:22.320 --> 00:46:25.710
so sometimes that's
80%, 90%, more--

00:46:25.710 --> 00:46:26.730
are not making money.

00:46:26.730 --> 00:46:29.563
That's a net cost for your
app, for your service,

00:46:29.563 --> 00:46:30.480
if you're on a server.

00:46:30.480 --> 00:46:31.830
They're sort of costing money.

00:46:31.830 --> 00:46:34.620
In some places that makes sense
because of networks and such.

00:46:34.620 --> 00:46:37.050
But in many cases they're
sitting there going,

00:46:37.050 --> 00:46:39.600
I really want to
monetize that group,

00:46:39.600 --> 00:46:45.120
but I want to take no chances
on this other group of users

00:46:45.120 --> 00:46:46.388
who are paying me money.

00:46:46.388 --> 00:46:48.180
I just can't afford to
take the risk there.

00:46:48.180 --> 00:46:51.340
So again, we went to
work here and we thought,

00:46:51.340 --> 00:46:53.640
how can we do this?

00:46:53.640 --> 00:46:57.710
So what if there was a
way to segment out smartly

00:46:57.710 --> 00:47:00.200
the users who are going to
spend and don't show them

00:47:00.200 --> 00:47:04.970
this ads experience from the
users who are almost certainly

00:47:04.970 --> 00:47:07.770
not going to purchase?

00:47:07.770 --> 00:47:11.370
And those users we want to go
ahead and put the personalized

00:47:11.370 --> 00:47:13.820
ad profile, and that's how
we'll make money off of them.

00:47:13.820 --> 00:47:15.156
And it's that simple.

00:47:15.156 --> 00:47:19.410
So here's an example.

00:47:19.410 --> 00:47:21.770
You've got the game on the
left in mission overview.

00:47:21.770 --> 00:47:23.932
And we segment this, we look.

00:47:23.932 --> 00:47:25.640
We use our machine
learning to figure out

00:47:25.640 --> 00:47:26.870
what's going on here.

00:47:26.870 --> 00:47:27.690
Who's the spender?

00:47:27.690 --> 00:47:28.190
OK.

00:47:28.190 --> 00:47:30.440
They follow the
path up at the top.

00:47:30.440 --> 00:47:33.780
Who's not the spender?

00:47:33.780 --> 00:47:35.730
Unlikely to make a
purchase, very unlikely

00:47:35.730 --> 00:47:36.668
to make a purchase.

00:47:36.668 --> 00:47:38.710
We send them through, we
give them ad experience.

00:47:38.710 --> 00:47:44.030
so we've tailored this to
the profile of the consumer

00:47:44.030 --> 00:47:48.420
and how they prefer to
help pay for the app.

00:47:48.420 --> 00:47:51.270
So this is pretty big
news because now we're

00:47:51.270 --> 00:47:56.530
taking a risk-free approach
to generate more revenue here.

00:47:56.530 --> 00:47:58.710
So, it's a first step.

00:47:58.710 --> 00:48:00.170
It's really easy to do this.

00:48:00.170 --> 00:48:01.920
When you go create an
interstitial ad unit

00:48:01.920 --> 00:48:02.830
right now--

00:48:02.830 --> 00:48:06.180
this is what we've
announced we're launching--

00:48:06.180 --> 00:48:08.310
there's a box that says,
smart segmentation.

00:48:08.310 --> 00:48:10.010
It's that simple.

00:48:10.010 --> 00:48:12.550
And then what we do is
we go ahead and look.

00:48:12.550 --> 00:48:14.230
We use our machines
to go figure out who

00:48:14.230 --> 00:48:16.120
are the spenders, the
likely spenders, who

00:48:16.120 --> 00:48:17.920
are the unlikely
spenders, and then

00:48:17.920 --> 00:48:20.500
we just start doing this
for you automatically.

00:48:20.500 --> 00:48:22.103
It's as simple as a checkbox.

00:48:22.103 --> 00:48:24.270
OK?

00:48:24.270 --> 00:48:25.650
And we've seen-- yeah.

00:48:25.650 --> 00:48:26.470
Here's an example.

00:48:26.470 --> 00:48:28.890
We've seen 30% increase
on ads revenue site

00:48:28.890 --> 00:48:33.710
because they've been introducing
ad units that they before

00:48:33.710 --> 00:48:37.107
were afraid to introduce because
it might have impacts on IAP.

00:48:40.450 --> 00:48:42.060
So that's what I've got.

00:48:42.060 --> 00:48:43.900
They're pretty
quick and tactical,

00:48:43.900 --> 00:48:45.755
but can make a huge difference.

00:48:45.755 --> 00:48:48.130
And I actually find these
things just so revolutionary to

00:48:48.130 --> 00:48:50.420
where we were one
year, two years ago.

00:48:50.420 --> 00:48:52.608
So, number one was,
really think about how

00:48:52.608 --> 00:48:54.775
this rewarded fits into the
game and the psychology.

00:48:54.775 --> 00:48:57.220
You heard that through
the sessions before.

00:48:57.220 --> 00:49:02.260
You can go to the
rewarded play option

00:49:02.260 --> 00:49:04.570
